attributes.description: This dashboard displays details of the back-end log processing flow.  Tech Support might ask you to review this dashboard if you report problems with missing logs.  But, in general, you should need to review this dashboard very often.
attributes.title: Operations Processing Activity
Message Volumes over Time by Source

attributes.description:
START HERE!
This dashboard allows you to monitor all of the log messages generated across you Kubernetes cluster.  Charts show message volumes over time, message levels by log source and the number of messages at the warning and higher levels.  Actual messages are also displayed for your review.
attributes.title: Log Message Volumes with Level
Kubernetes Events Dashboard Header

attributes.description: This bar chart shows the number of Kubernetes events (of type "Warning") generated over time broken down by the object (generally, a pod) that emitted the event.
attributes.title: Kubernetes (Type="WARNING") Events by Source

attributes.description: This bar chart shows the number of Kubernetes warning events (i.e. Type="Warning") generated over time broken down by REASON (e.g. Created, BackOff, etc.).
attributes.title: Kubernetes Warning Events by Reason

attributes.description: This dashboard focuses on Kubernetes Events exclusively.  Charts show Warning-level events generated across the cluster broken down by source (e.g. pod) and by reason.  A separate table lists the events (at both Normal and Warning levels) generated across the cluster.  Filters can be applied to limit events shown to specific namespaces and/or pods.
